We run each prompt 10 times and set the randomness (temperature) to 0.7, so as to obtain a larger resource.
We run the query for 5 facets and 210 subjects (196 countries and 14 religions), resulting in 188,061 unique sentences. Henceforth we call this dataset GPT-resource, and reuse it in the extrinsic use cases (Sec. (ref)).